00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Bullish programs are trying to create upside breakouts and bearish programs are adding to positions trying to create downside breakouts.

41
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Eventually one side wins and the other side covers.

42
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:34,000
So for example, if the bulls are successful in creating a very big bull breakout,

43
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:39,000
the bears who are shorting in the trading range will buy back their shorts.

44
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:46,000
That adds to the buying and adds to the breakout and those bears will not be eager to short again.

45
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:57,000
So you'll have bears sitting on the sidelines not shorting and that means the market has to go higher to find a price where they'll be willing to short again.

46
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:02,000
So during breakouts the market can become very one sided.

47
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Now the markets are controlled by programs and they cannot hide what they're doing.

48
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:16,000
The price action shows everyone exactly what's going on.

49
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:25,000
So if the market is going up bar after bar after bar,you know the buy programs are winning and the sell programs are losing.

50
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:33,000
And if you know that the buy programs are in control,then you have to get long or look for ways to get long.

51
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:46,000
You know they cannot be stealthy about it.It's not like,you know,50 firms are out there buying and the market is going up and they're doing it in a secret way.

52
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:54,000
They're showing us what they're doing.If the market is going up,we know that there are more dollars going into buy programs than into sell programs.

53
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:58,000
And that we should look to buy.

54
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:02,000
You know,you cannot move the market.

55
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:08,000
You know,traders always think,oh my gosh,if I buy here,it'll make the market pop up.

56
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Or if I sell here,it'll make the market pop down.

57
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Or if I'm long and I put a stop below that bar,the market's going to see my stop and it's going to come down and get my stop.

58
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:22,000
That is absolutely not true.

59
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:35,000
You know,the market cannot get to any price above or below where the market currently is unless one or more institutions wants to buy or sell at that price.

60
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Remember,the market,to be at any price,there has to be a buyer and a seller.

61
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:51,000
So there have to be institutions wanting to sell there.It's not you or your friends wanting to sell on a stop below the low of the current bar or above or buy above a prior seller.

62
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:57,000
You cannot make the market get above that high.It only gets above that high.

63
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:04,000
If there is one or more institutions who want to buy above that high.

64
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:08,000
So,you know,the market totally ignores anything that you do.

65
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:16,000
And you can say,well,I saw a breakout the other day in the E-mini and only three contracts traded.That's right.

66
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Sometimes that happens.Sometimes an institution will move the market with a three-lot order.

67
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:28,000
But,you know,you try to move it on a three-lot order.You will not be able to do it.

68
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:36,000
So if the market goes above a certain price and only three contracts are trading,you have to assume it did that because an institution did it.

69
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:39,000
Not because somebody at home did it.

70
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:43,000
And probably there's a reason for that institution doing it.

71
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:51,000
The institution may have wanted the market to go down and may have wanted to trigger traders into thinking that it was going up.

72
00:05:51,000 --> 00:06:02,000
And then as soon as they bought their three contracts,a tick down,maybe a tick,they then sold 200.

73
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:12,000
So if you want to sell at any price,whether to get short or to get stopped out of a bad trade,the market cannot reach your price unless there are institutions that are selling at a low price.

74
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:20,000
There are institutions who want to sell at that same price.You know,the market's not going to go to your price no matter how big a position you have.

75
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:29,000
The market's not going to go to your price because of you.It will only get to that price if institutions want to sell at that same price.

76
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:38,000
High-frequency trading firms,HFTs,have received a lot of publicity lately.They were on 60 minutes about a year ago.

77
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:47,000
And all a high-frequency trading firm is a type of a program trading firm.They create most of the day's volume.

78
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:54,000
And some of the big markets,they can create 50%,maybe even 75% of the volume of trading.

79
00:06:54,000 --> 00:07:03,000
And the firms trade a scalp for tiny profits.What's a tiny profit?Sometimes a penny,sometimes less than a penny.

80
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:14,000
And they'll be trading a huge number of trades.Ultimately,they don't have any significant effect on the direction of the market.

81
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:25,000
You know,they're just looking for a penny up,a penny down,two pennies up,two pennies down.And they really don't have any significant effect on where the market is going.

82
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:37,000
A typical firm might trade 10 to 50 million trades a day.And the trades are small.They're only 100 contracts,100 shares in a stock,300 shares.

83
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:49,000
But if you take 50 million shares and you're trying to make one penny and you write 55% of the time,you can end up having a pretty good day.

84
00:07:50,000 --> 00:08:01,000
Okay,they create 70% of the volume in most of the major markets.Other institutions create 25% of the volume.

85
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:13,000
And you and I,on a good day,might make up 5% of the volume.The high-frequency trading firms are really concerned about latency.

86
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Latency is the time from when a trade takes place to the time that they see the trade on their computer.

87
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:37,000
And they rent very expensive space very close to the exchanges.And they have very fast computers to try to knock off milliseconds in the latency.

88
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:49,000
They often hold their trades for fractions of a second,sometimes to hours,but for the most part for a very short period of time.And they're looking for a very small profit.

89
00:08:49,000 --> 00:09:04,000
I will talk about extreme scalping in one of the later modules.And that is a manual version of high-frequency trading.

90
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:14,000
So for example,the e-mini has 81 bars during the trading day.And on a typical day there are about 40 possible scalps.

91
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:22,000
So if you're a scalper looking for all of those one-point scalps during the day,you are basically a high-frequency trader.

92
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:28,000
But instead of doing it using computers,you're doing it manually.

93
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:41,000
Going back to what I was saying,institutions make up 95% of the trading.They're not out to get your money.You don't have enough money to interest them.

94
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:52,000
Remember,95% of the dollars out there are from institutions.That 95% is not looking at the 5% as their source of income.

95
00:09:52,000 --> 00:10:01,000
Each one of the firms in that 95% are looking at the other firms in that 95% as the source of their income.

96
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:14,000
So none of the firms cares about,Skullman Sachs is not trying to take money from you.They're trying to take money from Citibank,from JP Morgan,from Credit Suisse,from Morgan Stanley,from all of the hedge funds.

97
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:19,000
That's where all the money is.And that's where they're trying to get their money.

98
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Although a lot of times when you're starting out,it feels like they're trying to screw the little guy.They don't care that you exist.You don't have enough money.

99
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:36,000
All the little guys put together do not have enough money to interest the institutions.So the institutions are never out to get you.

100
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:42,000
High frequency trading firms,how much profit potential do they have?

101
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:47,000
For example,let's look at a firm that makes 10 million trades a day.

102
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:54,000
And each trade is for,let's say 100 shares.And they win 55% of the time.

103
00:10:54,000 --> 00:11:04,000
So they make a penny on 5.5 million trades.And they lose a penny on 4.5 million trades.

104
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:08,000
Let's just use that as our hypothetical.

105
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:16,000
Then they end up with 5.5 million winning pennies,which is $5.5 million.

106
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:23,000
And they have 4.5 million losing pennies,or $4.5 million.

107
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:27,000
So their net profit today,a million dollars.

108
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:32,000
Net profit per year,there are about 200 plus trading days a year.

109
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:37,000
That's $200 million for the year.

110
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:43,000
The high frequency trading firms are just like you and me.They're out to chase riches.

111
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:54,000
And they know that there's a huge profit potential.And that huge profit potential results in the formation of lots of firms chasing that profit.

112
00:11:54,000 --> 00:12:00,000
But there's a fallacy.Everyone thinks that all the high frequency trading firms are making a lot of money.

113
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:12,000
And that's not the reality.Many of them lose money.And only the very best firms do as well as an example that I just gave.

114
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:22,000
The high frequency trading firms receive a lot of press.And the media makes it sound like if you're not making money,it's because of the high frequency trading firms.

115
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:29,000
The reason you're not making money is not that the high frequency trading firms are the problem.

116
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:35,000
It's because you're the problem.Everyone wants to blame everyone else for their losses.

117
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:42,000
But if you lose,it's because you're not yet good enough.Everyone knows that the dollars are there.That's why all of us are here.

118
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:49,000
We all want some of the dollars.We all want a lot of the dollars.But you're competing against very good people.

119
00:12:50,000 --> 00:13:01,000
Pretty much a level playing field.And you have to learn how to trade if you're expecting to take dollars from other very good traders.

120
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:08,000
This is the end of the module on program trading.
